# Contact Us Requirements

## 1. Page Layout
- The **Contact Us** sidebar link must route to `/contact`.
- Page contains three PRD sections on one responsive layout:
  1. **Contact Details** — address, phone, email, office hours.
  2. **Contact Form** — name, email, designation (Student/Faculty/Admin), location, phone, subject, message.
  3. **Google Map** — embedded map iframe for the campus location (Chicago).

## 2. Form Validation (Client-Side JS)
- Validate on submit with inline field errors (no native browser-only validation).
- Rules: name required; email required + valid format; designation required (Student, Faculty, Admin); location required; phone required + valid format; subject required; message min 10 characters.
- Disable submit while posting; show success or server error feedback.

## 3. Server Integration
- POST ` /api/contact` persists messages via JSON file store on the Express server.
- Never log full message bodies to the browser console in production code.

## 4. Module Structure
- Keep UI under `client/src/modules/contact/`.
- Separate: `data/contactInfo.js`, `utils/validateContactForm.js`, `hooks/useContactForm.js`, `components/ContactDetails.js`, `components/ContactForm.js`, `components/ContactMap.js`, `ContactPage.js`.
- API client: `client/src/shared/api/contactApi.js`.

## 5. UX & Accessibility
- Use semantic headings, labels linked to inputs, and `role="alert"` for errors.
- Map iframe requires a descriptive `title` attribute.
- Match Super Travel styling and dark-mode theme overrides.
